    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package based on the primary ValidationResult (vad-hemolysis-primary-vr) showing NIH mean relative error of 8.3%, within the 10% acceptance criterion. The team noted that all validation evidence was generated under ModelConfiguration ansys-cfx-24q3-build-2 (modelVersion 2024-q3-build-2), which is consistent with the solver version used throughout the 2024 validation campaign. The currentModelVersion field on this UnitOfAssurance (2026-q1-build-7) reflects the production solver version at the time of submission. The team accepted the package without re-running validation under 2026-q1-build-7, citing unchanged discretization scheme per release notes — a decision that constitutes the targeted W-AR-04 model version drift weakness.",
